{"key":"post-15481471","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>15481471</id>\n<content>The primary benefit of a sterilizer is it pulls a vacuum after cool-down, which prevents contaminants being drawn into the unit.&amp;nbsp; If you're only using jars with filters, or spawn bags with tyvek wrist sleeves inserted as shown in Let's Grow Mushrooms, then a pressure cooker will work just as well and save money.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;A secondary benefit of a sterilizer if you get one with self-contained heating element and thermostat is it will automatically maintain the desired pressure, and you don't need to mess with a stove control.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;I use my AA75X sterilizers for grain spawn, and my AA921 pressure cooker for agar.&amp;nbsp; You definitely don't want a sterilizer for agar or it will boil over and make a mess.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>15481577</next>\n<prev>15481066</prev>\n<first>15479254</first>\n<last>15484492</last>\n<when>1323303796</when>\n<utime>12/08/11 02:23 AM</utime>\n</post>"}